# Requirements.txt Rule

When modifying requirements.txt, always verify that package versions exist on PyPI (https://pypi.org/).

## Verification Process

1. When adding or updating a package version in requirements.txt:
   - Check if the package name exists on PyPI
   - Verify that the specified version exists for that package
   - If version doesn't exist, either:
     - Remove the version constraint and use latest version (recommended)
     - Use an alternative version that is known to exist

2. For packages with version constraints (e.g., `package_name==1.2.3`):
   - Validate that both package name and version exist on PyPI
   - Ensure the version specified is valid and available

3. Best practices:
   - Prefer using the latest stable versions when possible
   - Avoid specifying exact patch versions unless absolutely necessary
   - Document reasons for pinning specific versions in comments

## Implementation Notes

This rule applies to all modifications to requirements.txt files, ensuring that all package dependencies are valid and can be installed by pip.